24/03/2004
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Interior Minister David Blunkett discussed bilateral co-operation in the fight against organised crime and trafficking with visiting Romanian counterpart Ioan Rus on Tuesday (23 March).
Blunkett pledged his country's support for Romania's EU integration bid and praised Bucharest's progress in accession talks and reforms.
In other news Tuesday, the defence ministers of Bulgaria and Romania agreed to co-operate in defending Bulgaria's Kozloduy nuclear power plant against air attacks.
Bulgarian batteries will be allowed to fire missiles over Romanian territory to intercept aircraft that veer off-course in the direction of the plant.
(Rompres, AFP, BTA - 23/03/04)
